Reasoning: The paper discusses modeling the meaning associated with collections of documental entities, which is a topic that falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of the World Wide Web as a paradigmatic example suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of digital libraries (cs.DL) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper's emphasis on probabilistic data and context effects suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
